wikipedia_page.main: Michael John Brown (11 April 1944 – 9 March 2021) was an English footballer who played as a forward in the Football League.

response: Born in Colchester, Dennis began his career as a youth player at hometown club Colchester United. He made his debut as a substitute for Micky Brown in the 13th minute of a 2–0 victory against Lincoln City on 22 April 1970. He made five appearances for the U's, playing his final game for the club just under one year after his debut in a 4–0 defeat at Oldham Athletic before leaving to join Dover.
